quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,61,"Then, when the Messengers (the angels) came unto the family of Lût (Lot)."
  15,62,"He said: "
  15,63,"They said: "
  16,40,"Verily! Our Word unto a thing when We intend it, is only that We say unto it: ",footnotes:1:(V.40) See the footnote of (Verse 51:30)
  16,41,"And as for those who emigrated for the Cause of Allâh, after they had been wronged, We will certainly give them goodly residence in this world, but indeed the reward of the Hereafter will be greater; if they but knew!"
  16,42,"(They are) those who remained patient (in this world for Allâh’s sake), and put their trust in their Lord (Allâh Alone)."
  17,7,"(And We said): "
  17,8,"[And We said in the Taurât (Torah)]: "
  17,9,"Verily, this Qur’ân guides to that which is most just and right and gives glad tidings to the believers (in the Oneness of Allâh and His Messenger, Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم), who work deeds of righteousness, that they shall have a great reward (Paradise)."